paragraphs.text: a very old friend, came by today. 'cause he was tellin' ev'ry one in town 'bout the love that he just found. and marie's the name of his latest flame.
he talked and talked, and i heard him say. that she had the longest blackest hair, the prettiest green eyes any where. and mari's the name of his latest flame.
though i smiled, the tears in side were a burnin'. i wished him luck and then he- said goodbye. he was gone but still his words kept returnin'. what else was there for me to do but cry.
would you believe, that yesterday. this girl was in my arms and swore to me. she'd be mine eternally. and marie's the name, of his latest flame.
